article.description: — Terence Lewis II poured in a career-high 28 points and snagged 10 rebounds as Jackson State held off Mississippi Valley State 69-65 on Saturday.
article.headline: Lewis leads Jackson St past Mississippi Valley St 69-65
article.linkText: Lewis leads Jackson St past Mississippi Valley St 69-65
article.story: ITTA BENA, Miss. -- — Terence Lewis II poured in a career-high 28 points and snagged 10 rebounds as Jackson State held off Mississippi Valley State 69-65 on Saturday. Jamarcus Jones had 11 points and 12 rebounds for the Tigers (5-16, 3-7 Southwestern Athletic Conference), who ended a four-game skid. Jonas James III added 10 points and eight assists. Ken Evans Jr. had 10 rebounds. Jackson State scored 43 second-half points, a season high for the team. Caleb Hunter had 16 points for the Delta Devils (1-19, 1-9), who have now lost seven straight games.
